sentences: Im Na-yeon (Korean: 임나연; born September 22, 1995), known mononymously as Nayeon, is a South Korean singer.
After participating on the reality survival television show Sixteen in 2015, she became a member in the South Korean girl group Twice formed by JYP Entertainment.
On September 15, 2010, she secretly attended JYP Entertainment's 7th Open Audition after which she became a trainee.
In 2013, she was initially cast as a member of 6mix, a JYP girl group that was planned but never debuted.
She also made an appearance in the second episode of KBS2's 2012 Korean drama Dream High 2.

section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: In 2015, Nayeon participated in the reality television show Sixteen, a competition designed to choose the founding members of Twice.
section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: In October 2015, Nayeon officially debuted as a member of Twice with their first extended play, The Story Begins.
section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: In Gallup Korea's annual music poll for 2017, Nayeon was voted the sixth most popular idol in South Korea, ahead of all her bandmates.
section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: In the 2018 poll, she was again ranked sixth, receiving 6.7% of the votes.
section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: In 2019, she was ranked fifth, receiving 8.2% of the votes.
section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: In 2019, Nayeon was also ranked as the eighth most popular female K-pop idol in a survey of soldiers doing mandatory military service in South Korea.
section: == Life and career == | === 2015–present: Sixteen and Twice ===

sentences: During trainee years, Nayeon became a model for brands such as Smart School Uniform and TN.
In May 2021, she became a model and appeared in the promotional video for Chaumet's Joséphine Collection.
In August, she became a model for Biotherm Korea, a South Korean beauty brand.
